You are in The Kitchen.
You can see a Fillet Knife.
You can go east or north.

You can barely elbow your way into the kitchen around the parade of waitstaff and sous chefs who work around the clock to sate the voluptuary appetites of the wealthy passengers. Four ovens sit against the walls and each seems to be constantly in use. The sounds and smells of searing, simmering, bubbling and frying buzz in your ears. Heat, smoke, and steam occasionally impede visibility until fans and vents blow them out.

A sliding door to the north leads to the larders.
