This room is the larder for the guests; as such, feasts of fine ingredients are stored in ammonia-cycle refrigerators. The walls are misty with heat put off by the expensive, clunky refrigeration units. One entire wall stores wine meant for cooking as well as drinking, and the cabinets contain canned and jarred goods.

The sliding door to the south leads back to the kitchens.
