You can go northwest.

Ivy climbs trellises up the walls of this sunlit game room. Its checkerboard floor offers a small walkway through groups of bright wicker chairs and tables where ladies play cards and men roll dice on painted game boards. Although light floods in from the windows overlooking the ocean, a series of bulbs are attached to the ceiling, which is decorated with white inset panels and gold leaf.
