This room is comprised of a glorious skylight overhead, looking up through to the weather deck, a hard, tile floor, and a series of wooden slats over the walls. It is filled with a host of the latest physical fitness and calisthenics devices, including a rowing machine, cycling machine, and weight lifting machine. There is also a rack of clubs for exercising the arms, and an electric horse stands nobly in the corner awaiting anyone brave enough to ride it.

A woman who must be the ship's personal trainer paces the room, carefully observing the passengers' efforts.
