You are in The Engine Room.
You can see Howard Blaine.
You can go north.

Even the most modern steam engines sound like demons, and the beating heart of the beautiful Prinzessin is no different. Here, the engine hisses uproariously, a cantankerous dragon with a boiler for a stomach lurking beneath the gilded palace above. Walkways guarded by iron rails stand between you and the thundering pistons, swirling and spinning, as syncopating pressure gauges dance their thin black needles up and down.

Although this room is where you spend most of your time on board the ship, you are keenly aware that one wrong move could see you ground into pulp by the ceaseless thrumming of the pistons.

North leads back to the Lower Deck.
